      <h1 class="title">Mythbusting IV Therapy – Separating Fact from Fiction</h1>

      <div class="blog-content">
        <p>
          Intravenous (IV) therapy has become very popular in Dubai. It delivers fluids, vitamins,
          and minerals directly into your bloodstream for rapid rehydration and a fast nutrient
          boost. Yet many people still ask:
          <i>Is it safe? Does it hurt? Don’t I get enough vitamins from food and water?</i>
          In this guide, we bust the biggest myths, share the facts, and answer your FAQs so you can
          decide if an IV therapy session is right for you.
        </p>

        <h4>1. Myth: “IV Therapy Is Painful and Invasive”</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Ultra‑fine needles feel like a quick pinch, not deep pain.</li>
          <li>Expert nurses ensure first‑try success in safe IV placement.</li>
          <li>Relaxed setting: recliner, soft music, and phone time.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>2. Myth: “IV Therapy Is Unsafe, It’s Only for Hospitals”</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Sterile, single‑use supplies every time.</li>
          <li>Physician‑approved formulas tailored to your needs.</li>
          <li>Nurses trained and equipped for rare emergencies.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>3. Myth: “If I Eat Well and Drink Water, I Don’t Need IV Drips”</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Oral supplements absorb 20–50%; IV delivers nearly 100%.</li>
          <li>Hydration in 20–30 minutes versus hours with water.</li>
          <li>Balanced electrolytes for nerves and muscle function.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>4. Myth: “IV Therapy Is Just a Fad”</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Used in hospitals since the early 1900s for dehydration.</li>
          <li>Supports chemotherapy patients with recovery and tolerance.</li>
          <li>
            Wellness use: IV vitamin C can reduce cold symptoms faster; B12 boosts energy and mood.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h4>5. Myth: “I’ll Overdose on Vitamins”</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Safe, controlled dosing based on guidelines.</li>
          <li>Water‑soluble vitamins flush harmlessly via urine.</li>
          <li>Kidney screening before each session for added safety.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>6. Myth: “Anyone Can Give an IV, It’s Not Technical”</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Certified nurses with advanced IV therapy training.</li>
          <li>Standard protocols from Infusion Nurses Society.</li>
          <li>Regular DHA inspections for safety and compliance.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>7. Myth: “IV Drips Are Only for Hangovers or Celebrities”</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><b>Hangover Relief:</b> Saline, B vitamins, electrolytes.</li>
          <li><b>Immunity Boost:</b> Vitamins and minerals to strengthen defense.</li>
          <li><b>Beauty Drips:</b> Nutrients for skin glow and hair strength.</li>
          <li><b>Athletic Recovery:</b> Magnesium and amino acids for muscle repair.</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>8. Myth: “IV Therapy Is Too Expensive”</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Base sessions from AED 850, with bundle savings.</li>
          <li>Faster recovery saves time and costly doctor visits.</li>
